STL Short Notes

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
    Mental shortcut
        Need sorted + unique?                   → set
        Need sorted + duplicates?               → multiset
        Need fast lookup, order doesn’t matter? → unordered_set

    Real-world examples
        set             → leaderboard ranks (unique scores, sorted)
        multiset        → inventory with duplicate items
        unordered_set   → “already seen IDs” / cache / fast membership test

    One-liner summary
        Tree-based containers (set, multiset) care about order.
        Hash-based containers (unordered_set) care about speed.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Mental shortcut
        Sorted + unique keys            → map
        Sorted + duplicate keys         → multimap
        Fast lookup, order irrelevant   → unordered_map

    Real-world examples
        map             → configuration settings (unique keys, ordered)
        multimap        → student → multiple courses
        unordered_map   → caches, symbol tables, lookup tables

    One-liner summary
        Tree maps care about order.
        Hash maps care about speed.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------